Project outputs:
- Enhanced capacity of the State Agency on State Financial Control and Fight against Corruption;
- Clear guidelines on budgetary issues developed and people are more aware on state budget, its resources, development and expenditures;
- Public awareness on corruption and its consequences improved and stigmatization of corruption increased.

Project outputs:
- Transparency and Accountability: Assessments and trainings for increasing transparency and accountability of the system of governance and the Security Sector;
- Human Rights: Capacity building for system of   internal control and accountability within the Public Sector  and promotioion of Effective Public Complaint Mechanism (PCM);
- Judicial reform: Promote newly adopted Criminal Procedures Code and assist Juvenile Justice.

Project outputs:
Module 1 Objective: Government and Civil society capacity to prevent corruption is strengthened.
Module 1 outputs:
Output 1: ASFCFAC strengthened in its ability to carry out sector specific awareness rasising / prevention campaigns;
Output 2: Civil society organizations able to engage effectively at local and Agency level over corruption issues and facilitate local solutions to problems;
Module 2 - Objectives: Schools are able to identify corruption risks and design appropriate responses.  Ministry of Education is able to mainstream corruption prevention approaches across the country;
Module 2 Outputs:
Output 1: ASFCFAC and CSOs understand the drivers of corruption in secondary education and have developed tools to address it;
Output 2: Good practice on dealing with corruption in schools is used throughout the country.

